		  one-loop results, we then derive and give semianalytical
		  forms of the two-loop contributions for both the cosmic
		  density and velocity propagators. These results are tested
		  against numerical simulations and shown to significantly
		  improve upon one-loop results for redshifts above 0.5. We
		  found however that at lower redshift two-loop order
		  corrections are too large partly due to a strong
