		  terms of the two-point correlation function if the
		  clustering follows a hierarchical form. Use of the Poisson
		  errors greatly misestimates the covariance matrix when N
		  becomes large and leads to underestimates of the
		  uncertainties on the fitted parameters of model correlation
		  functions. The new covariance matrix formula is shown to be
