		  used to demonstrate that the input cosmological model can
		  be correctly recovered. We discuss in detail the possible
		  differences between the galaxy and mass power spectra, and
		  treat these using simulations, analytic models and a hybrid
		  empirical approach. Based on these investigations, we are
		  confident that the 2dFGRS power spectrum can be used to
		  infer the matter content of the universe. On large scales,
		  our estimated power spectrum shows evidence for the `baryon
		  oscillations' that are predicted in cold dark matter (CDM)
		  models. Fitting to a CDM model, assuming a primordial ns= 1
