		  peak type. We discuss a simple estimate of nonlinear
		  evolution and illustrate the effect of the peak bias on the
		  redshift space multipoles. For k 0.1 h/Mpc, the peak bias
		  is deterministic but k-ependent, so the configuration space
		  bias is stochastic and scale dependent, both in real and
