		  level for DA(z) and H(z) in several redshift bins. This, in
		  turn, implies errors of sigma(w)=0.03 0.05 for a constant
		  dark energy equation of state in a flat universe. Deep
		  galaxy cluster surveys such as the planned South Pole
		  Telescope survey can extend this test out to z??1 or as far
