		  predict the effect of baryons on the weak-lensing signal at
		  scales corresponding to multipole moments 100<l<10,000, we
		  find that baryons may change the lensing power spectrum by
		  less than 0.5% at l<1000, but by 1% to 10% at
		  1000<l<10,000. The size of the effect exceeds the predicted
