		  incorporated. It is found that the slope of the
		  scale-dependent bias on large scales is determined only by
		  the behavior of primordial bispectrum in the squeezed limit
		  and is not sensitive to bias models in general. It is the
		  amplitude of scale-dependent bias that is sensitive to the
		  bias models. The effects of redshift-space distortions turn
		  out to be quite small for the monopole component of the
		  power spectrum, while the quadrupole component is
		  proportional to the monopole component on large scales and
		  thus also sensitive to the primordial non-Gaussianity.},
