		  literature of the scale-dependent bias in the presence of
		  multiple Gaussian source fields as well as higher-order
		  coupling to cover the models described by
		  frequently-discussed fNL, gNL and tNL parameterization. We
		  find that the resultant power spectrum is characterized by
		  two parameters responsible for the shape and the amplitude
		  of the scale-dependent bias in addition to the Gaussian
		  bias factor. We show how (a generalized version of)
		  Suyama-Yamaguchi inequality between fNL and tNL can
		  directly be accessible from the observed power spectrum
		  through the dependence on our new parameter which controls
		  the shape of the scale-dependent bias. The other parameter
		  for the amplitude of the scale-dependent bias is shown to
		  be useful to distinguish the simplest quadratic
		  non-Gaussianities (i.e., fNL-type) from higher-order ones
