		  spheres with radius 8h-1Mpc). We argue that redshift-space
		  distortion measurements will help to determine the physics
		  behind the cosmic acceleration, testing whether it is
		  related to dark energy or modified gravity, and will
		  provide an opportunity to test possible dark energy
		  clumping or coupling between dark energy and dark matter.
		  If we can measure galaxy bias in addition, simultaneous
		  measurement of both the overdensity and velocity fields can
		  be used to test the validity of equivalence principle,
		  through the continuity equation.},
